SIMPLE: transgress
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transgress
<hw>Trans*gress"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Transgressed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Transgressing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>transgresser</ets>. See <er>Transgression</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To pass over or beyond; to surpass.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Surpassing common faith, <qex>transgressing</qex> nature's
law.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to overpass, as any prescribed as the limit
of duty; to break or violate, as a law, civil or moral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For man will hearken to his glozing lies,⟦br⟧
And easily <qex>transgress</qex> the sole command.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To offend against; to vex.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why give you peace to this imperate beast⟦br⟧
That hath so long <qex>transgressed</qex> you ?</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transgress</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transgress
<hw>Trans*gress"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To offend against the law;
to sin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who <qex>transgressed</qex> in the thing accursed.</q> <rj><qau>I
Chron. ii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transgression</ent>⟦br⟧
